HEADWORD: Lotos-eater
<hw>Lo"tos-eat`er</hw>
<pr>(l⟦omac⟧"t⟦ocr⟧s-⟦emac⟧t`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>One who ate the fruit or leaf of the
lotus, and, as a consequence, gave himself up to indolence and
daydreams; one of the <membof>Lotophagi</membof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mild-eyed melancholy <qex>Lotos-eaters</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>louche</ent>⟦br⟧
